'''Watto's Junkshop''', later named '''Wald's Parts''', was a junk shop owned by [[Watto/Legends|Watto]], a [[Junk dealer/Legends|junk dealer]], in the [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Mos Espa/Legends|Mos Espa]] on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. When [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] was a little boy, he worked here as well as his mother, [[Shmi Skywalker Lars/Legends|Shmi]] and Anakin's [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] friend [[W. Wald]]. Anakin and Wald worked as mechanics while Shmi was just a simple worker. The catch phrase was "What do you want?" or "Hi chuba da nago?" in [[Huttese/Legends|Huttese]]. The shop's best customers were [[Jawa/Legends|Jawas]] who were always looking for salvage.

It was well-stocked despite being one of the city's smallest businesses. Watto based much of his business on his dealings with [[Jawa/Legends|Jawas]], and only accepted Tatooinian currency. The top of the shop featured a bell-shaped apex, which Watto built to resemble the nest from [[Toydaria/Legends|his homeworld]].

In [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]], [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]] visited Watto's shop looking for a [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]] replacement for the [[J-type 327 Nubian royal starship/Legends|Queen's Royal Starship]], a [[T-14 hyperdrive generator/Legends|T-14 hyperdrive generator]].

After retiring, Watto turned ownership to Wald, who renamed it ''Wald's Parts''.

==Structure==
[[File:QGJAniWatto-TPM.png|thumb|left|220px|Qui-Gon Jinn negotiates with Watto as Anakin Skywalker looks on]]
For a simple-minded Toydarian like Watto, his shop was a fairly complex building. It stood out from many of the other stores and market booths that infested Mos Espa, which partially accounted for the greedy shopkeeper's success.

The main area of the shop was the base of the building itself, where most of Watto's droid technology and smaller machinery was located. Moisture vaporators, calibration devices, [[Moobian torsion valve/Legends|moobian torsion valves]] and even a droid lubrication bath were some of the items included. Watto used a [[scenter]] to make it smell like [[Toydaria/Legends|his homeworld]].

[[File:ITW1_Watto_Shop.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Watto's Shop cutaway]]
Above the base was a strange bell-shaped top, held up by [[Durasteel/Legends|durasteel]] support rings, that attracted the most attention and therefore customers. It was meant to be reminiscent of the muck nests of [[Toydaria/Legends|Toydaria]], and was in fact Watto's perch. Included in the nest was a trophy shelf of [[Podracing/Legends|podrace]] memorabilia, including a victory chain won by [[Sebulba/Legends|Sebulba]] and a glove recovered from [[Bekk Tunit/Legends|Bekk Tunit's]] crash site. It also included [[polyfiber]] netting containing Toydarian muck lake atmosphere. To maintain a comfortable temperature, the durasteel double walls of the shop were supported by a layer of coolant flowing in between. Warm air was vented out through slots in the shop's skirt and top.

Outside was an arched portal leading into a junkyard, where Watto kept his largest vehicle parts, including turbine engines, hyperdrives, and various other machinery. This area was the main portion of his shop and earned him much [[Wupiupi/Legends|wupiupi]].

==Behind the scenes==
The [[EVA Pod]] from the [[1960s|1968]] film [[Wikipedia:2001: A Space Odyssey|''2001: A Space Odyssey'']] can be seen in the background of Watto's junkyard.

